---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const baseRaw = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/';
const base = baseRaw.endsWith('/') ? baseRaw : baseRaw + '/';
const withBase = (path: string) => base + path.replace(/^\/+/, '');
---
<BaseLayout title="Pitch Deck — TRIAD" description="TRIAD: Quantum-Inspired Layer-1 Blockchain. Problem, solution, technology, metrics, roadmap, security, market, tokenomics.">
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-12">
      <header class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">TRIAD: Quantum-Inspired Layer-1 Blockchain</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-mist max-w-3xl">Quantum‑inspired L1 with wave‑interference consensus on a DAG, built in Rust. Fast, green, accessible Web3.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Introduction</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/80 text-sm">
            TRIAD is a revolutionary Layer‑1 protocol inspired by quantum mechanics, designed to overcome scalability, speed, and energy efficiency limitations of modern blockchains.
            Built on Rust with open‑source code on <a class="underline hover:text-white" href="https://github.com/fillay12321/TRIAD" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>, TRIAD leverages wave‑interference consensus in a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG).
            Our mission is to make Web3 fast, green, and accessible to millions.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-white/80 text-sm">Try the demo:</p>
          <pre class="mt-2 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-black/40 p-3 text-xs"><code>cargo run --release --example quantum_consensus_demo</code></pre>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">The Problem</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Ethereum:</b> 15–30 TPS, high fees, slow confirmations.</li>
            <li><b>Solana:</b> Thousands of TPS but prone to outages and centralization risks.</li>
            <li><b>Aptos/Sui:</b> Parallelism via complex BFT, demanding heavy hardware.</li>
            <li><b>Avalanche:</b> Probabilistic consensus without field‑based scoring.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70 text-xs">Bottlenecks in ordering, verification, and CPU/GPU utilization hinder DeFi, gaming, and payments — Web3 isn’t ready for mass adoption.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Solution: TRIAD</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/80 text-sm">Transactions are “waves” interfering in a DAG field. Constructive interference enables fast, probabilistic consensus without heavy voting rounds.</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Speed:</b> 11–13K TPS peak, 8–9K sustained (local demo). Target 25.8K TPS.</li>
            <li><b>Energy Efficiency:</b> Minimal rounds and compact messages.</li>
            <li><b>Parallelism:</b> Rust + Rayon, static sharding, Ed25519 batch verification.</li>
            <li><b>Openness:</b> MIT license, community‑ready.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">How TRIAD Works</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/80 text-sm">Consensus pipeline per round (500 tx):</p>
          <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Batch generation</li>
            <li>Sharding into parallel lanes</li>
            <li>Wave construction: amplitude (A), phase (φ), TTL</li>
            <li>Parallel signing: Ed25519 via Rayon (~15–16 ms / 500)</li>
            <li>Batch verification: ed25519‑zebra (~7–8 ms / 2×250), fallback dalek</li>
            <li>Interference: compute field per shard (~18–25 ms, CPU; GPU planned)</li>
            <li>Decision: Accept/Reject based on constructiveness, fees, conflicts, TTL, reputation</li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Performance Metrics (local demo)</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Round Time:</b> 43–60 ms</li>
            <li><b>Peak TPS:</b> 11–13K</li>
            <li><b>Sustained TPS:</b> 8–9K (500 tx/round)</li>
            <li><b>Settings:</b> TRIAD_WAVE_SIG_BATCH=500, RAYON_NUM_THREADS=4</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70 text-xs">Note: Local metrics; distributed tests are in development.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Architecture & Technology</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Language:</b> Rust; Rayon for CPU parallelism</li>
            <li><b>Sharding:</b> Static per‑round</li>
            <li><b>Cryptography:</b> Ed25519 (dalek for keys/single; zebra for batches); BLS planned</li>
            <li><b>DAG:</b> Causal consistency without linear chain</li>
            <li><b>Performance knobs:</b> TRIAD_WAVE_SIG_BATCH=500, LTO fat, panic=abort</li>
            <li><b>Future:</b> GPU (OpenCL/CUDA), libp2p/QUIC, dApp adapter</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Competitive Comparison</h2>
          <div class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
              <thead class="text-white/70">
                <tr>
                  <th class="py-2 pr-4">Protocol</th>
                  <th class="py-2 pr-4">TPS (L1)</th>
                  <th class="py-2 pr-4">Consensus</th>
                  <th class="py-2 pr-4">TRIAD Advantages</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/10">
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Ethereum</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">15–30</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">PoS</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">~1000x faster locally</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Solana</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Thousands</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">PoH + BFT</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Simpler, more energy‑efficient</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Aptos/Sui</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Thousands</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">HotStuff + parallel</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Lighter, batch‑friendly</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Avalanche</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Thousands</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Probabilistic</td>
                  <td class="py-2 pr-4">Unique field‑based scoring</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70 text-xs">TRIAD excels in parallelism and lightweight consensus but is currently a demo.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Security</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/80 text-sm"><b>Current:</b></p>
          <ul class="mt-1 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Ed25519 signatures with invalid wave filtering</li>
            <li>Batch verification (zebra) with fallback (dalek)</li>
            <li>Deterministic logging for auditability</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-white/80 text-sm"><b>Planned:</b></p>
          <ul class="mt-1 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>BLS for validator aggregation</li>
            <li>Formalized interference security proofs</li>
            <li>libp2p/QUIC, Noise, DoS protection</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-white/80 text-sm"><b>Limitations:</b> Local demo, CPU‑only, no adapter, no formal resilience proofs yet.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Market & Potential</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Market Size:</b> $10B (2023) → $469B by 2030 (CAGR 87%)</li>
            <li><b>Target Niches:</b> DeFi, gaming, payments</li>
            <li><b>Use Cases:</b> instant payments, real‑time gaming, AI integrations</li>
            <li><b>Edge:</b> quantum‑inspired design and energy efficiency for sustainable Web3</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Roadmap</h2>
          <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Phase 0 (0–2 mo):</b> Demo hardening, key caching, batch stabilization, build optimization</li>
            <li><b>Phase 1 (2–4 mo):</b> SIMD/AVX2, GPU kernels, benchmarks</li>
            <li><b>Phase 2 (4–7 mo):</b> libp2p/QUIC, global finality, BLS aggregation</li>
            <li><b>Phase 3 (7–10 mo):</b> Interoperable adapter, SDKs, wallet integrations</li>
            <li><b>Phase 4 (10–14 mo):</b> AI/ML for dynamic resharding and anomaly detection</li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Economics & Tokenomics</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>TRIAD Token (TBD):</b> staking, fees, governance</li>
            <li><b>Staking:</b> validators earn from wave processing</li>
            <li><b>Fees:</b> dynamic, weighted by interference</li>
            <li><b>Governance:</b> probabilistic voting</li>
            <li><b>Financing:</b> community bootstrap; seeking investors for Phases 1–2</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Team & Community</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Creator:</b> Independent developer (fillay12321), expert in Rust and blockchain</li>
            <li><b>Community:</b> X (<a class="underline hover:text-white" href="https://x.com/TRIADBlockchain" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@TRIADBlockchain</a>) and <a class="underline hover:text-white" href="https://github.com/fillay12321/TRIAD" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
            <li><b>Plans:</b> Discord/Telegram, hackathons, contributor grants</li>
            <li><b>Partnerships:</b> seeking GPU/network engineers and security researchers</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Why TRIAD?</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Speed:</b> Millions of tx for DeFi, gaming, payments</li>
            <li><b>Sustainability:</b> Green consensus with minimal energy use</li>
            <li><b>Accessibility:</b> Interoperable adapter & SDKs simplify dApps</li>
            <li><b>Decentralization:</b> Planned network ensures global finality and resilience</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70 text-xs">By 2026, TRIAD aims to power everything from micropayments to metaverses.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5 md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Join TRIAD</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 text-white/80 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><b>Developers:</b> Clone the repo, run the demo, submit PRs on <a class="underline hover:text-white" href="https://github.com/fillay12321/TRIAD" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
            <li><b>Investors:</b> Contact <a class="underline hover:text-white" href="mailto:team@triad.dev">team@triad.dev</a> for partnerships</li>
            <li><b>Enthusiasts:</b> Follow <a class="underline hover:text-white" href="https://x.com/TRIADBlockchain" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@TRIADBlockchain</a> and spread the mission</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <a href={withBase('documentation')} class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg border border-white/20 bg-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm hover:bg-white/15">← Back to Documentation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
